      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Skewed residuals and outliers in linear regression are a real headache, but don't panic! You can try transforming your dependent variable, $Y$, to bring the distribution closer to normal. Transformations like the natural logarithm ($\\ln(Y)$) or the square root ($\\sqrt{Y}$) are common starting points. If those don't work, you might consider using a different model, like a generalized linear model (GLM) with a different error distribution, which is often more robust to non-normal data. Remember, sometimes the data itself is just inherently messy, which is a lot like the state of a typical market!",
